Cape Town - A suspect believed to be behind eight bank robberies has made his first appearance in court. Sinako Magi, 32, made a brief appearance at the Bellville Magistrate’s Court on Monday and will be back in the dock in June. He is facing charges of armed robbery. The State is set to prove that Magi carried out eight robberies at Standard and Absa Banks in Bellville, Gugulethu, Kleinvei and Kuilsriver between November 2021 and March. He was arrested by the Hawks.  Hawks spokesperson Zinzi Hani said Magi was arrested in the Khayelitsha area on Friday. “It is reported that the accused would walk into a bank and demand cash. “The accused has been charged with armed robbery. The robberies date back to November 2021. “The accused remains in custody and the matter is remanded to June 6 for legal representation.” Weekend Argus